title: Taking Humor Seriously on “The Simpsons”
excerpt: David Owen’s 2000 Profile of George Meyer: Humor has to reframe reality, Meyer says. “It’s like seeing in two dimensions and then opening the other eye or looking through a View-Master and suddenly seeing in three.”

title: John Swartzwelder, Sage of “The Simpsons” | The New Yorker
excerpt: The first major interview with one of the most revered comedy writers of all time.
